  "prompt": "What are the different grade levels and titles at Deloitte Consulting US?",
  "response": "At Deloitte Consulting in the United States, the career progression typically follows a structured path with distinct grade levels and corresponding titles. Below is a general outline of the hierarchy, though titles and responsibilities can vary slightly based on specific practices (e.g., Strategy & Operations, Technology, Human Capital) or roles.\n\n---\n\n### **Entry-Level Roles**\n1. **Analyst (Business Technology Analyst, Strategy Analyst, etc.)**\n   - Fresh graduates or early-career professionals.\n   - Focus on data analysis, research, and supporting project teams.\n\n2. **Consultant**\n   - Slightly more experienced than Analysts.\n   - Takes on broader responsibilities, including client interactions and delivering project components.\n\n---\n\n### **Mid-Level Roles**\n3. **Senior Consultant**\n   - Leads specific project workstreams.\n   - Manages junior team members and serves as a key client contact.\n\n4. **Manager**\n   - Oversees entire projects or large workstreams.\n   - Responsible for client relationships, team leadership, and project delivery.\n\n---\n\n### **Senior-Level Roles**\n5. **Senior Manager**\n   - Manages multiple projects or large, complex engagements.\n   - Plays a significant role in business development and client strategy.\n\n6. **Director / Principal**\n   - Focuses on high-level client relationships and strategic initiatives.\n   - Drives practice growth and thought leadership.\n\n---\n\n### **Leadership Roles**\n7. **Managing Director (MD)**\n   - Senior leadership role with a focus on business development and practice leadership.\n   - Often responsible for managing a portfolio of clients or a specific practice area.\n\n8. **Partner**\n   - The highest level in the consulting hierarchy.\n   - Focuses on firm leadership, client strategy, and major decision-making.\n\n---\n\n### Notes:\n- Progression through these levels typically requires a combination of experience, performance, and business development skills.\n- Titles may vary slightly depending on the specific consulting practice (e.g., \"Solution Specialist\" in Technology roles).\n- Deloitte also offers specialized career tracks, such as technical or industry-specific roles, which may have slightly different titles.\n\nFor the most accurate and updated information, it\u2019s always best to refer to Deloitte\u2019s internal resources or discuss with HR.",
